Installer for the quantracker APM toolchain

Designed to enable the toolchain to be installed easily on various operating systems.

Currently supported by Linux and Windows2000

Dependencies.

For Windows, it is suggested to download and install MINGW and MSYS.
  You will need the g++ and binutils packages
  in a MSYS shell type migw-get
  Select the bin class for:
    mingw32-base
    mingw32-binutils
    mingw32-g++
    mingw32-libgcc
    mingw32-libstdc++
    mingw32-api

For Linux
  Most linux distros should already have most of the dependencies.

  Download the sources and invoke make in the source directory.
